7 An Act relating to the Tulsa Reconciliation Education
and Scholarship Program; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
8 Sections 2621, 2623, and 2625, which relate to
creation of and eligibility for the program;
9 providing purpose of program; modifying eligibility
for program; increasing income limit for certain
10 eligibility; directing income limit to be adjusted
annually; exempting certain applicants from certain
11 income limit; allowing certain form to be used to
verify income; removing certain eligibility criteria;
12 directing the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
Education to give first priority status to certain
13 applicants; modifying process for verifying
documentation of lineage; directing certain rules to
14 include certain criteria; requiring application form
to include certain language; removing language
15 authorizing annual award of scholarships to certain
students; directing the State Regents to involve
16 certain community advisory committee in selection
process; providing for composition of and
17 appointments to advisory committee; directing certain
university president to submit a list of proposed
18 members; directing advisory committee to review
certain applications and make certain
19 recommendations; directing the State Regents to
select recipients from certain list; prescribing
20 income limitation for eligibility retention; limiting
the number of scholarships that may be awarded to
21 certain students; defining term; directing certain
students to be given priority; allowing certain
22 grants and scholarships to be used on certain
expenses; directing certain applicants to always be
23 given first priority status; updating statutory
language; and declaring an emergency.
24
